<br>
Eldratu is a wonderful person. She is my friend. She is still my friend. I still like Eldratu.<br>
<br>
I know Eldratu is hurting right now. She feels like her feelings were not taken into consideration. She was a member of the guild and was a member of the guild for a long time.<br>
<br>
Maybe this will help make it more understandable for folks bashing Eldratu..<br>
<br>
When you are comfortable with the way a guild is, and you do not want to be guilded with people who are of a race that is considered technically: evil, then when your guild does not take your feelings into consideration, and despite your protests, guilds that person, it would definitely seem like a stab in the back. It would also feel like your guild was saying: suck it up, you're not important, this person being in our guild is more important than you being in our guild, because if you left over this, we wouldn't care. Them banning her from the boards for posting her opinion screams: We don't care what you think ,and we do not want to listen to it -- despite the fact you're ranting, we value your opinion so little that we're removing your ability to make your opinion heard to us all in private. Them removing her from the guild shouts to her: We wanted Mhordel more than we wanted you. Get over it. See ya later chickey, because we got tired of hearing your crap. Too bad you couldn't suck it up.<br>
<br>
I want to say that I do not think that is what her guild intended. I'm saying that from what Eldratu has said, it sounds like this is the feeling she is having .. what she feels like her guild has done to her. I could be wrong, but if you read everything she's said, what I've posted above  would feel like a likely scenario if you were in her shoes.<br>
<br>
Like anyone, I personally will not be blackmailed or held over the coals to do something based on someone elses threats. Not to mention, the entire guild voted on this thing, and most of them agreed to it. Eldratu, as much as I adore her, was being a tiny bit selfish in expecting that just because -she- doesn't want an evil person in the guild, then, to silence her dissent, they simply shouldn't do it, because she is a member of the guild too. Fact is, this stance simply doesnt' wash sweetie..<br>
<br>
Eldratu == it is unfair to expect that your guild would not do something the majority of them agreed to, just because one or two people disagreed with it. Despite the fact that you were in the guild sooo long, and did so much work, the thing is -- many of these people have the same rights you do, and those rights include changing their minds, and helping to change the guild policy by voting and agreeing on it. One or two people disagreeing with this change isn't going to make a difference. I'm sure if 1/2 or even 1/4th of the guild didn't like the idea, they'd of rethought it out. But thing is.. from what they've said, this isn't the case.<br>
<br>
A guild is perfectly within rights to change its mind Eldratu -- how is that lying? They said they posted, and that people voted. How is this lying? How is this stabbing you in the back?<br>
<br>
I will tell you something. As an administrator, if someone went around badmouthing my 'area', or guild as it were.. if they ignored us, turned off guild chat, went annonymous, and continued to harass guild members -- if i had the complaints from other guild mates to do it, I would remove that person from the guild.<br>
<br>
No area administrator is going to make their other guildmates/area mates suffer because one person is making them unhappy and uncomfortable.<br>
<br>
How do I know this? Because I've done it. I've had to kick people out of my area because they made it difficult for others to enjoy it and their time there. I didn't want to have to do it, because that person had contributed, and been there for a while, but the fact is that when it comes down to the line, you have to do what is best for the guild as a whole.<br>
<br>
Please think on this, consider it carefully. Eldratu, sweetie, you're a wooonderful person. You've always been so helpful and understanding -- so why are you having so much trouble accepting that your guild, as a democratic majority, decided to make some changes to the guild policy? That is what happened here. It isn't about catering to one or two people's needs, but what the guild decided it wanted as a whole. You should respect your fellow players and their decisions, and do your best to stop haranging them for making that decision because you didn't like it.<br>
<br>
I hope.. I really hope this helps people to understand where Eldratu may be coming from -- including her guildmates, and helps Eldratu understand that its not just about one person here, but about -everyone-.<br>
<br>
